The paper focuses on analyzing abusive behavior in Twitter, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to classify users and tweets. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category, as it deals with the analysis of social media data. Additionally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category, as the paper involves NLP techniques to analyze text data. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category, as the paper deals with the societal impact of cyberbullying and cyberaggression. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category, as the paper discusses potential mechanisms for Twitter to suspend abusive users. Finally, cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, as the paper does not focus on software development, but rather on analyzing social media data.
